data.title: OXYGEN LEAK
data.text:
The colonists have reported hearing a faint hissing sound
coming from the vicinity of Airlock B.

Due to the high cost of adhesive sealant strips (duct tape),
it is recommended that colonists use Airlock A for all future
 egress/ingress. Also try and hold your breath more often.

data.title: HAVE A SPACE CIGAR
data.text:
The board of investors likes your style, kid.
Have a cigar, you're gonna go far.

(The SMARS Corporation is not in any way responsible for
fires related to lighting cigars inside the habitation module)

data.title: ECONOMIC DOWNTURN ON EARTH
data.text:
The board of directors regretfully has to inform you that,
due to the ongoing financial uncertainy of Earth's economy,
your colony's funding has been reduced, effective immediately.

data.title: LET THE SUN SHINE
data.text:
The high winds in this region have kept your base's solar panels
unexpectedly dust-free and efficient, boosting their output
above our expectations.

Your colony's power reserves have been increased.

data.title: SMARTIAN MOONSHINE
data.text:
Your science team has discovered that it is possible to
reconfigure one of the water recyclers to convert some
of your potato crop into vodka.
Doing so would require sacrificing some of your food
supply, but it might be good for the crew's spirits!

data.title: WEALTHY DONOR
data.text:
A billionaire on Earth has decided to donate to your
terraforming efforts, in the hopes that if things ever get really
bad on Earth, he can maybe crash at your place for a bit.
Seems like a lot of people have been asking that lately...

We told him thanks, and that should the need arise,
we'll definitely see what we can do.

data.title: FIRE!
data.text:
A fire has broken out in one of your modules, caused in part
by a misunderstanding of the meaning of the word 'inflammable.'

We can either fight the blaze with our precious water supply,
or preserve our water, and contain the fire and let it burn itself out.

resolutions.text: Water is too precious! (lose $ and air)

data.title: DR GREENTHUMB
data.text:
Your colonists must have some green thumbs,
as the last few potato harvests have been unusually bountiful!

Your food supplies have increased. What can one
do with so many 'taters?
